baseName.value: Prefabricated concrete panels: 01 Pan all sp 20

generalComment.value:
For the LCA study, specific data (primary data) were used for the processes concerning the internal manufacturing steps at the ISOCELL plants in Pognano. Also specific are the distances calculated by the suppliers of the raw materials used and the quantities and number of used to transport them to the plant (primary data).
In addition, primary data from EPDs published by suppliers covering all raw materials were used.
Where generic data were used (e.g. for the schematisation of production processes associated with the various input materials), they were chosen to be representative by geographical area and technological methodology.

With regard to the production process, reference was made to the entire production of panels prefabricated panels in the Pognano plant for the year 2022. In addition, the data referring to the cubic metre of prefabricated panel product was reported to the square metre of panel using the "ratio of cubic metres (m3) divided by square metres (m2) of total produced panels" as allocation factor.

The inventory data considered in the study represent at least 95 per cent of the total inflows (mass and energy) of phases A1, A2 and A3. What is not included in the LCA has been specified.
Cut-offs include air emissions produced during the welding activities at ISOCELL plants.
